                "invention-title": [
                    "Preparation method of Pd/ZnO/g-carbon nitride composite nanomaterial for hydrogen detection",
                    "一种用于氢气检测的Pd/ZnO/g-氮化碳复合纳米材料的制备方法"
                ]
            },
            "abstract": [
                {
                    "p": "The invention discloses a preparation method of a Pd/ZnO/g-C3N4 composite nanomaterial for hydrogen detection, which comprises the following steps: firstly, taking urea as a raw material, carrying out heat treatment to form g-C3N4, forming a layer of metal-organic framework material with an MOF structure on the surface of g-C3N4, then taking PdCl2 as a noble metal source, anchoring PdCl2 molecules on the surface of the material through a dipping-freeze drying technology, and carrying out vacuum drying to obtain the Pd/ZnO/g-C3N4 composite nanomaterial for hydrogen detection. The preparation method comprises the following steps: firstly preparing a metal-organic framework material, then performing in-situ reduction to form Pd clusters, finally removing an organic part in the metal-organic framework material through heat treatment, forming a large number of pore structures with specific sizes in the material, enabling the pore structures to be beneficial to preferential adsorption of hydrogen, and then utilizing a catalytic reaction of the Pd clusters to H2 to improve the response sensitivity of the composite material to the hydrogen. The method provided by the invention is simple in preparation and low in cost, and is expected to greatly improve the application of the nano material in the field of hydrogen detection."
                },
                {
                    "p": "本发明公开一种用于氢气检测的Pd/ZnO/g‑C3N4复合纳米材料的制备方法，首先以尿素做原料通过热处理形成g‑C3N4，在其表面形成一层具有MOF结构的金属‑有机框架材料后，用PdCl2做贵金属源，通过浸渍‑冷冻干燥技术将PdCl2分子锚定在材料表面，然后原位还原形成Pd团簇，最后通过热处理将金属‑有机框架材料中的有机部分去除，在材料内部形成大量特定尺寸的孔隙结构，该孔隙结构有利于氢气的优先吸附，然后利用Pd团簇对H2的催化反应，提升复合材料对氢气的响应灵敏度，本发明提供的方法制作简单，成本低，有望大幅提升纳米材料在氢气检测领域的应用。"
                }
            ]
